    <item>
      <title>A Forage Filter System?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=9630#M9630</link>
      <description>Sony's new expansion is going to introduce a buff filtering system, which got me to thinking why not a foraging filtering system? &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I play a 70 druid with a foraging skill that has been long maxed out at 200. Once forage gets to 200 you never NOT forage anything. I've also invested AAs in all three levels of Nature's Bounty, an AA ability that gives me a chance to forage two things at once. Since I'm currently working on my baking and brewing skills, I find foraging to be an invaluable tool.  I also love being able to help out my guildmates who need foraged items for their tradeskills and can't forage themselves.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;However, as you can imagine I often find myself foraging a LOT of worthless stuff that I don't need. Rabbit meat, roots, fishing grubs, myriad of different pounds of meat in GoD zones, tradeskill items that my friends and I no longer need, etc.  The most annoying to me are epic forages I keep making when passing through those zones for an epic that I completed years ago.  Anyway, I'd love for there to be a way to filter out items that I no longer want to forage and would have just destroyed anyway.  This doesn't mean I want to be able to get nothing but rare forages (some forages are made purposely rare I'm sure ~sighs and wishes she could get more air-infused water~)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;What I had in mind was a filtering system that would essentially allow me to select items I no longer want to keep when I forage. In the event that I forage an item on the DO NOT WANT list, I would instead get a message: "You have foraged something on your filter list, so it has automatically be destroyed."  (Or since I'm a roleplayer I'd love to see a message more along the lines of, "You have foraged something that you no longer want, so you have discarded it."). &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Anyway, I think this would be a very useful tool for foragers, though I have a feeling it's not useful enough for the population on the whole for Sony to take the time to implement. (Druids and rangers are the ones that would benefit from this the most I think and they hardly make up a majority although bards and certain races can forage some too). Nevertheless I thought I'd bring the idea out here to see what others thought. :) &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Right before I decided to post this, I did a search to see if this idea had been brought up recently. Someone did come up with this exact same idea almost as year and half ago, but most message boards frown on resurrecting old threads so I thought I’d go ahead and start a new topic as planned. Here’s a link to the old thread though:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=1347&amp;highlight=forage+filter#M1347</description>
