    <item>
      <title>Re: A Forage Filter System?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=9778#M9778</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;A forage filter defeats the purpose of forage. What you get is supposed to be random, and some items are meant to be rarer than others and are supposed to take a long time to find. If you could just walk into a zone, forage, and pick out what you wanted the foraged item to be from a list, of course everyone would go for the rares and before you know it, every tradeskiller in the game has items that are supposed to crop up only a few times a year for sale in bazaar and the economy for those items is basically ruined because of all the competition driving prices down. It is the randomness and rareness of certain forages that makes them worth looking for. A forage filter would destroy that by making rare items common.</description>
