      <title>Re: A Forage Filter System?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=9781#M9781</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;hr&gt;Vegeta-X wrote:&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;A forage filter defeats the purpose of forage. What you get is supposed to be random, and some items are meant to be rarer than others and are supposed to take a long time to find. If you could just walk into a zone, forage, and pick out what you wanted&amp;nbsp;the foraged&amp;nbsp;item to be from a list, of course everyone would go for the rares and before you know it, every tradeskiller in the game has items that are supposed to crop up only a few times a year for sale in bazaar and the economy for those items is basically ruined because of all the competition driving prices down. It is the randomness and rareness of certain forages that makes them worth looking for. A forage filter would destroy that by making rare items common.&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;You totally missed the point of the forage filter. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;It's not for making rares easier to get. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;It's merely a setting to automatically toss things we don't want. Say I'm in East Karana, and only want tea leaves, with everything else on the forage filter. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I forage. Get a pod of water. It's automatically destroyed, with a message saying something akin to "You foraged a pod of water, but tossed it away since it's not what you're after."&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I forage again, and get a plains pebble, which is then tossed. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The only time an item actually appears on my curser, would be when it's a tea leaf. Or whatever I haven't blocked. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The chance of getting items you don't want will still be there, but this way we dont' have to constantly be destroying things, or dropping things, or having no drop, non-stackable items we dont' want taking up inventory. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
