g those who use them. If Sony is going to start giving you the tools as part of the game that they currently ban, it makes their position concerning cheaters weaker and encourages more players to take a chance. I imagine many will get caught right away, but the cleverest ones will always find ways to cover their tracks and this game has enough cheaters as it is and doesn't need anymore because Sony showed signs of weakness by allowing certain portions of banned macros, eventually leading to the entire banned macro, into the game.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
